                        <provenance>
                            <!--   The manuscript comes from the area of Gondar. The name of the original owner or patron, <persName ref="Takla Maryam"/>, is indicated in the main hand as 
                            <foreign xml:lang="gez">ገብርኪ፡</foreign>, ‘your servant’, in the supplication formula on <locus target=""/>.
                            The name of a secondary owner, <persName ref="Walatta Sion"/>, is indicated on <locus target="#2ra"/> on a previously erased name.
                            The name of <persName ref="Walatta Petros"/> is also indicated in the ... .-->
                            The manuscript was looted by <roleName type="title">ʾAṣe</roleName> <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros"/> and entered the 
                            <placeName ref="INS0101MadhaneAlam"/> collection in <placeName ref="LOC4547Maqdal"/> .
                            The manuscript was then brought to <placeName ref="wd:Q21">England</placeName> after the 1868 expedition by <persName ref="PRS7484Napier"/>. 
                            The subsequent owners are unknown in detail. The book was sold to the <placeName ref="INS0525Quaritch"/> and
                            eventually purchased by <persName ref="PRS5782JuelJen"/> at an auction at Sotheby's 
                            on 20 March 1983, according to the auction catalogue.
                        </provenance>
